		{
			"id": 1,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "Different glucocorticoid hormones ( GCH ) show differences in the intensity and in the kinetics of their immunomodulating activity . <S>",
			"relation": "BACKGROUND"
		},
		{
			"id": 2,
			"parent": 1,
			"text": "The mechanism ( s ) of action of GCH is under investigation ,",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 3,
			"parent": 2,
			"text": "but is has been noted that they exert immune activity via the genomic pathway . <S>",
			"relation": "COMPARISON"
		},
		{
			"id": 4,
			"parent": 0,
			"text": "We have studied the effects of prednisone ( PDN ) , deflazacort ( DFC ) , and dexamethasone ( DXM ) on the production of cytokines",
			"relation": "ROOT"
		},
		{
			"id": 5,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "( IL-2 , IL-6 , TNF-alpha , IL-10 )",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 6,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "by peripheral T lymphocytes , and the effects on the inhibition of NF-kB DNA binding activity by activated Jurkat cell line . <S>",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT"
		},
		{
			"id": 7,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "The data",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 8,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "obtained",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 9,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "show that the three GCH molecules exert an immunosuppression on cytokine production by T lymphocytes and a strong decrease in the nuclear translocation of NF-kB in Jurkat cells ;",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT"
		},
		{
			"id": 10,
			"parent": 7,
			"text": "moreover , ( a ) not all the cytokines",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 11,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "investigated",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		},
		{
			"id": 12,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "were affected , and not with the same intensity , by the three GCH",
			"relation": "SAME-UNIT"
		},
		{
			"id": 13,
			"parent": 10,
			"text": "and ( b ) DXM inhibited the binding activity of NF-kB less than that of DFC and PDN . <S>",
			"relation": "ADDITION"
		},
		{
			"id": 14,
			"parent": 4,
			"text": "These data are in agreement with the concept",
			"relation": "FINDINGS"
		},
		{
			"id": 15,
			"parent": 14,
			"text": "that different GCH compounds might differ in their binding and affinity properties , tissue-specific metabolism , and interaction with transcription factor . <S>",
			"relation": "ELABORATION"
		}
	]
